Well, life has been insane lately. But to wrap it all up into one cryptic nuttshell, here is some Pedro the Lion lyrics:

I just aced my Psych exam. In a class where %30 of the class is failing and the averedge is 70%, IT FEELS PRETTY FUCKING GOOD!

Yes that's right. After binge drinking saterday night, waking up sunday morning with the worst hangover ever and then not sleeping yet, the ipod is the only thing holding my sanity together at work. If it where to fail I would collapse in a wretched tweaked out heap. hour and a half to go.

When I don't sleep for over 24 hours I get really worried. I don't know, paraniod, anxious, deppressed. And then I want to have sex with things, but besides the last part, all bad.

My lungs feel like burning.

Strong Bad is really Tom Waits in a mexican wrestler's mask.

They are the same fucking person!

I was just ask by a PSE union representative at our union meeting to become a Membership Organizer. This would mean travel, experiance, excitement, and a chance at other lucrative job oppurtunities. One step closer to my gaol.

I'm bloody giddy and sick to my stomach.

I just purchased a 30gig I-pod today from the internets. I had it engraved with the lyrics from my favorite song of all time. "December's tragic drive a new face, soul reborn" And no it's not Kenny Loggins
On another note, it's snowing in Arlington and the gusts must be at least 50mph. The power should go out so I can go home.
I can't believe it's fucking snowing right now.

I just got really depressed and frustrated doing research for my POCI class. Supposed to be researching federalism, and I stumble across one article about over 23% of the money earmarked for AIDS prevention was given to Christian groups so that they can teach "all those dirty fags and niggers" not to have sex. What the fuck. How the hell do you "teach" someone to be abstinent? Are there fidelity textbooks out there? AND YES. BEHOLD, THE BIGGEST DOUCHE IN THE UNIVERSE:
He looks kinda young. I guess I won't feel that bad when I beat the bloody shit out of his fuck-face. By the way, if you didn't know, Timmy is responsible for the $30 tabs, cuts to social services, and just recently, at our state capitol, stood up and opposed a law that would make it illegal to discriminate against homosexuals. You know, just like it's illegal to discriminate against blacks, women, and OTHER HUMANS. It's actually the same bill. They just throw the word fag on there and call it good. BUT NOOOOOO not good for Timmy. Churches and Christian Institutions across the state are already voicing their support for the anti-Christ up there. Which I lump into the doucheness. Maybe the discharge, yes. THEY ARE THE POST-DOUCHE DISCHARGE. fuckbags

My Political science teacher just gave me a B- on my first paper for no real particular reason. He said it was a great paper but that I should take more and quote more from the text.

I see. So that warrents a 16/20? Especially since you didn't state any criteria except for "Write a paper on the differences between state and federal constitutions".

I think it might have something to do with the fact that I pionted out he was all but absent from the first weeks discusions.

Whatever, go to bed Jesse.

Took Nathaniel and co. out for Nate's 21st birthday last night to pioneer square to go barhopping. While trying to keep up with the little fucker I found myself to be possibly the most intoxicated I have ever been. Then vomiting ensued, then four hours of sleep, then work at seven this morning. Needless to say I feel like poo. 

P.S. not being able to smoke in bars totally sucks. I agree with it... but it sucks.

fell like death I had a great time though. Good seeing some people I only comment with.

Finished my application, letter of intent and update on my resume today for the attendance specialist position. God I hope I get this job. Also finished the invitations for the work christmas party
Sorry, you can only come if you work for Arlington Public Schools. So I have to plan that and still go christmas shopping and send presents. I also have to be at Sea-tac airport tommorow at bloody 10 in the morning for a big union delagate meeting and go to josies party in Tacoma in the evening (wich I need directions to). Got my textbooks in the mail yesterday. I'm stoked for classes to start. Played Sarah a song last night. "I will follow you into the Dark" by Death Cab for Cutie. Pragmatic is playing a christmas show on the 23rd. Hopefully the guys will come through and learn some christmas songs. Hopefully I'll see some LJ friends there as well. It's at the Chrome Cafe in Arlington. For more info: www.myspace.com/pragmatic I have to order a new power adapter for my hard drive (blew up), get a christmas tree, pay more bills, put up a new mailbox, and get a copy of Microsoft word for my lappy. pLus much more that I can't remember now. Even though I have all this stuff to do, and my head is pounding, it makes me content. I seem to like stress.

So I've been thinking and evaluating. Even after two more years of school at $275 per credit I could not possibly find a job that could pay me as much as I make now.

It seems I have been rushing feverishly to attain something that is monitarily useless to me. It is more of a conquest. Maybe spirtual or maybe just to say I could achieve it.

Nevertheless I entend on sticking with it. In the end if I have a masters it would be nice to fall back on it when I'm older. 

ugh, so many things.

turns concrete to black,
drop by drop,
never stop,

For every tear,

The homogony of my lover,
As lay down at our sides,

Every curve illuminated,
Every move sedated,

turns concrete to black,
drop by drop,
never stop,
The rain is all we have, love,
And I must be getting back,

turns concrete to black,

never stop,

Yes, I purchased a Pro Tools M Box on Friday and I finally downloaded the software after many painstakingly dreadfull processes today.

Now I can go home and use my new Groove Tubes condenser mic and actually record something. Woot!

On another note, thanks to the Arm for the two full disks of mp3's. Including albums by the likes of Wolf Parade, Criteria, and Clap Your Hands and Say Yeah.

Also some atrocious radiohead demos from back in the day.
